description:
&lt;p&gt;Looking for a flexible working opportunity?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a caring and empathetic Healthcare Assistant with experience of working with children with complex health needs? Do you enjoy delivering family-centred care and working one to one with children and young people? Are you reliable, punctual and adaptable? If so, this could be the opportunity for you. We are looking for Healthcare Assistants to join our team to deliver quality holistic care. This is a great way to work around your personal commitments, while having the opportunity to develop and learn new skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for Healthcare Assistants who have experience of enteral feeds and administration of nebulized medication. Past experience in caring for children who require seizure management or have a tracheostomy with or without ventilation will be beneficial. The ability to communicate and interact with children, including those with learning difficulties, in a variety of ways, is vital, as well as fluent spoken and written English. You should be computer literate and able to write clear and accurate clinical notes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Healthcare Assistant, you will provide a high level of respite care to children and young people – this will include initiating and organising sensory play activities for the children in your care. At times you may work with children with challenging behaviour so experience in this area is beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate a two shift pattern of 11.5 hours, seven days a week and require applicants to be able to work weekday, night and weekend shifts.  This part time role is for 9 shifts per four week rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please click apply to complete your application and supporting statement outlining why you would suit the role and would love to work with us.&lt;/p&gt;
